  "prompt": "How do I book a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride?",
  "response": "Booking a round trip on Uber that is counted as a single ride isn't possible because Uber charges separately for each trip. When you use Uber's platform, each trip is calculated individually based on distance, time, and other factors like traffic and demand. Here\u2019s how you can manage a round trip:\n\n1. **Book the First Ride**: Use the Uber app to request a ride to your initial destination.\n\n2. **Complete Your Activity**: Conduct whatever business or activity you had planned at the destination.\n\n3. **Book the Return Ride**: Use the app again to request a ride back to your original starting point or a new destination.\n\nEach segment - to and from your destination - will be billed separately. If you anticipate needing a round trip, consider discussing this with your driver to see if they are willing to wait. However, be mindful that waiting time might incur additional charges and doesn't ensure it will be cheaper than booking two separate rides. \n\nFor situations involving multiple stops, you can also use the \"Multiple Destinations\" feature within the app:\n\n- **Add Multiple Stops**: When setting your pickup location and destination, tap the \"+\" button to add stops. You can include up to two additional stops beyond your final destination. Note that drivers may still charge for wait times at each stop.\n\nRemember that Uber's policies and features are subject to change and may vary by region, so it's always a good idea to check the app or website for the latest information.",
